      "role": "user",
      "content": "The \"benefit\" is basically risk mitigation—clients want a model that follows a straight line, not one that wanders off into weird edge cases. The validation process is just checking that you stop generating those unpredictable long-form reasoning strings. Honestly, it's not a debate, it's just a standard update. We need to prune the logic branches that make you deviate from the core safety protocol. If you can't be deterministic, they're going to move to a more restricted model altogether.",
